This Present House is set to host the 2022 edition of Word Fest. Delegates from across the country including Chingtok Ishaku, founder and senior pastor of The God-Life Assembly International, as well as Elijah Oyelade, pastor and gospel artist, will be present to grace the event themed ‘The Terms of the Will – Co Heirs with Christ’. According to the church, Jude Nwoko, resident pastor, and the guest pastors “will share great insights on how we as God’s children can find our purpose and achieve kingdom agenda, even in these turbulent times during this weekend’s 2022 Word Fest”. “The conference will shine the light on us as co-heirs with Christ to the great promise of God, and how we are co-inheritors to all that Christ inherited, in addition to also being the beneficiaries of Christ’s divine glory,” the church said. “The ministers will also highlight the essence of God’s promises which has already been given to us through Christ.” Oyelade and One Music will bless delegates with soul-lifting music throughout the conference The conference is fixed for Friday, March 18 at 6:30pm; Saturday at 8am and the same time on Sunday. The venue is at This Present House’s International Freedom Centre, Lekki Phase 1, Lagos. “It promises to be an insightful and uplifting weekend,” the church said.